1
00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )
2
00:00:08,560 --> 00:00:11,960
{\an8}That is not necessary.
I want her to be present.

3
00:00:12,560 --> 00:00:15,159
{\an8}Mom, can you let me
discuss with her first?

4
00:00:15,160 --> 00:00:18,960
{\an8}I want you to make a decision today.

5
00:00:19,880 --> 00:00:23,480
{\an8}What's all this? What's going on?

6
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:33,440
{\an8}Radwa. I've come here
to tell Thariq to divorce you.

7
00:00:35,520 --> 00:00:38,400
{\an8}And marry Raudhah.

8
00:00:46,560 --> 00:00:50,759
If you think you love your family,
and respect me

9
00:00:50,760 --> 00:00:53,360
as the mother who gave birth to you...

10
00:00:54,440 --> 00:00:57,399
- Let Thariq go.
- Mom, that's enough.

11
00:00:57,400 --> 00:01:01,519
Shut up! I want an answer now!

12
00:01:01,520 --> 00:01:04,079
Look at her. She can't wait anymore!

13
00:01:04,080 --> 00:01:08,559
Soon, everyone will notice
her growing belly.

14
00:01:08,560 --> 00:01:12,599
Okay, then. You should leave first.
We can discuss this another day.

15
00:01:12,600 --> 00:01:16,520
I won't leave
until you make your decision.

16
00:01:20,200 --> 00:01:21,800
Radwa.

17
00:01:25,320 --> 00:01:28,680
I want you to agree.

18
00:01:30,920 --> 00:01:32,120
Say it!

19
00:01:33,680 --> 00:01:34,920
Say it!

20
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:36,720
I agree.

21
00:01:38,160 --> 00:01:39,400
I do.

22
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:44,320
But I'm asking you to go back first.
We'll discuss tomorrow, okay?

23
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:47,320
Are you sure?

24
00:01:48,160 --> 00:01:50,040
If you don't come,

25
00:01:51,680 --> 00:01:52,839
I will come here.

26
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:54,840
Mom, please.

27
00:02:02,160 --> 00:02:03,720
Dear...

28
00:02:32,640 --> 00:02:34,480
{\an8}Do you want to die or stay quiet?

29
00:02:50,640 --> 00:02:52,240
Treasure.

30
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:56,839
If you want to cry, then cry. Let it out.

31
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:59,400
Don't keep it. It'll make it worse.

32
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:02,920
Just cry. Go.

33
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:06,799
Darling, aren't you angry?

34
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:09,239
Mom forced me to divorce you

35
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:11,559
and marry Raudhah instead.

36
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:14,280
Don't you feel angry?
If I were you, I'd be really mad.

37
00:03:14,920 --> 00:03:17,439
I know you're mad. Let it all out.

38
00:03:17,440 --> 00:03:21,159
Scream if you have to! Just scream. Go!

39
00:03:21,160 --> 00:03:22,320
Go!

40
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:39,919
How could Mom do this to me?

41
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:45,000
I know I was wrong.
But I'm still her daughter!

42
00:03:47,880 --> 00:03:53,080
Since I was young, I never felt her love.

43
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:58,880
No hugs, no laughter, no tenderness.

44
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:04,480
When I grew up,
I no longer cared about all that.

45
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:09,000
I still supported them. 100%!

46
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:15,560
But why are they taking away
my only happiness?

47
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:19,398
And you agreed to it!

48
00:04:19,399 --> 00:04:22,439
You agreed to marry Raudhah
because she can conceive.

49
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:24,960
- She can. And I couldn't!
- Darling.

50
00:04:25,560 --> 00:04:27,400
Listen to me.

51
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:30,920
I don't even want children.

52
00:04:31,960 --> 00:04:34,520
And I didn't agree.

53
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:39,840
I only did that because I don't want
to see you hurting like this.

54
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:43,240
Darling.

55
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:48,960
No matter what,

56
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:52,720
I won't ever leave you.

57
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:09,680
It's okay.

58
00:05:16,520 --> 00:05:18,440
Falah?

59
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:21,200
Falah?

60
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:34,679
Falah?

61
00:05:34,680 --> 00:05:36,800
Where are you?

62
00:05:40,760 --> 00:05:42,320
Falah!

63
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:45,800
Where are you, Falah?

64
00:05:46,840 --> 00:05:48,640
Falah!

65
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:54,520
You said you won't leave me again.

66
00:06:13,320 --> 00:06:15,759
- Hello?
<i>- Hello, Ridz.</i>

67
00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:17,480
It's Fateh.

68
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:19,559
What's the matter?

69
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:23,519
<i>It's Falah, my friend. He's gone.</i>

70
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:28,079
- Gone?
- He was sleeping next to me.

71
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:32,439
But when I got up, he's suddenly gone.

72
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:35,159
Listen, Fateh. Go back to sleep.

73
00:06:35,160 --> 00:06:37,360
Tomorrow, I'll come
and we'll look for Falah together.

74
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:40,280
Okay, Ridz.

75
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:58,519
Ridz, that night,
he was sleeping next to me.

76
00:06:58,520 --> 00:07:02,400
- Okay.
- But when I woke up, he was suddenly gone.

77
00:07:04,920 --> 00:07:06,080
Maybe he ran away?

78
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:09,639
He wouldn't do that at night.

79
00:07:09,640 --> 00:07:11,640
He's scared of the dark.

80
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:16,759
Maybe he's staying
somewhere else, not here?

81
00:07:16,760 --> 00:07:21,039
Not possible. He loves it here.

82
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:23,880
He promised me he won't go anywhere.

83
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:30,039
- Ridz.
- Yes.

84
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:34,440
Falah was kidnapped,
just like the other kids.

85
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:36,880
Wait.

86
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:40,120
Kidnapped?

87
00:07:46,440 --> 00:07:48,680
Fateh, take this.

88
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,160
Don't ever take it off.

89
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:55,560
If you feel you're in danger,
press this button.

90
00:07:58,080 --> 00:08:01,560
- I'll come.
- Okay, Ridz.

91
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,879
What's your problem?

92
00:08:17,880 --> 00:08:21,239
Mom did it her way, but nothing changed.
Now let me teach you a lesson.

93
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:23,719
You're rude. You humiliated Mom and Dad.

94
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:26,959
Just agree with their decision.
What's so hard about it?

95
00:08:26,960 --> 00:08:29,239
What do you mean? That's enough!

96
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:32,879
Don't you think Mom's idea was ridiculous?
Divorce me?

97
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:36,479
- And then he has to marry Raudhah?
- That's the perfect idea.

98
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:39,120
You don't deserve your husband.

99
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:42,599
There are other men out there.
Why does it have to be my husband?

100
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:44,200
Because you're too dumb!

101
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:48,079
You can't even use his money
for your own family.

102
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:50,959
- Just give him to Raudhah.
- Come on. It's 2025.

103
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:53,359
Not even kids in dramas
fight for money like you.

104
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:54,480
Don't touch me!

105
00:08:55,160 --> 00:08:56,400
I don't care.

106
00:08:57,200 --> 00:09:00,960
I want you to make
your husband divorce you.

107
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:06,240
- Okay, fine. I agree.
- Okay.

108
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:09,399
But with one condition.

109
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:12,599
Ask your husband to divorce you first.
Then, I'll marry him.

110
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:15,599
- Are you stupid?
- Yes, I am.

111
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:17,679
Too stupid to entertain
your stupid requests.

112
00:09:17,680 --> 00:09:23,240
I don't care. I will make sure
you divorce him willingly.

113
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:27,200
Get lost!

114
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,560
Don't ever come here.

115
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:32,360
Leave!

116
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:57,040
Ridz, pick up. Please.

117
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:06,720
A child went missing
from Teduh last night.

118
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:10,120
Under the care of...

119
00:10:11,680 --> 00:10:12,880
Datin Zizi.

120
00:10:13,760 --> 00:10:16,399
A friend of Radwa's adopted sister.

121
00:10:16,400 --> 00:10:21,719
Fateh said before he went to sleep,
that kid was in the room.

122
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:23,800
But he woke up at 1 a.m.

123
00:10:25,240 --> 00:10:26,400
He saw the other kid is gone.

124
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:28,960
Kidnapped?

125
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:30,720
It's not confirmed yet.

126
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:33,119
Okay.

127
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:36,639
Go to Teduh.
Make sure your theory is right.

128
00:10:36,640 --> 00:10:39,359
- Then, we can plan what to do.
- Sure.

129
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:45,119
Wait. If Zahid's dead,
and children are still going missing,

130
00:10:45,120 --> 00:10:46,840
maybe someone else is involved.

131
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:50,439
I think there's someone else above Zahid.

132
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:51,960
What about his phone?

133
00:10:52,560 --> 00:10:54,240
Could you trace who sent the message?

134
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:57,520
We just got the lab results.

135
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:03,239
It's empty. Clear.

136
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:05,680
Nothing's left.

137
00:11:29,520 --> 00:11:31,480
That's a long sigh.

138
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:36,400
Why?

139
00:11:37,560 --> 00:11:38,640
What do you mean?

140
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:43,440
Why do men in uniform

141
00:11:44,440 --> 00:11:46,079
always turn out to be failed fathers

142
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:48,880
and husbands who neglect their wives?

143
00:11:50,680 --> 00:11:52,080
Do you want to know why?

144
00:11:54,920 --> 00:11:58,720
But they're not all like that.

145
00:12:00,320 --> 00:12:02,560
It's fine. I still want to know.

146
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:08,800
As you know,
my dad used to be in the military.

147
00:12:10,920 --> 00:12:13,400
They don't have fixed working hours.

148
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:17,680
They go on operations and are always busy.

149
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:20,600
I know all that.

150
00:12:21,880 --> 00:12:23,760
But as a son,

151
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:27,200
I never had any memories with my dad.

152
00:12:29,120 --> 00:12:31,920
My mom managed everything at home.

153
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:36,960
But I know she was suffering inside.

154
00:12:38,160 --> 00:12:40,239
But do you think

155
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:43,559
he failed as a husband
and as a dad because of that?

156
00:12:43,560 --> 00:12:45,560
Because he didn't have time
for his family?

157
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:53,240
I wouldn't hate it
if that were the only reason.

158
00:12:54,760 --> 00:12:57,280
But killing his own wife and children?

159
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:04,279
- I can't accept that.
- What do you mean?

160
00:13:04,280 --> 00:13:09,320
Did you know that depression
can kill someone?

161
00:13:11,920 --> 00:13:14,600
Mila, do you know Falah?

162
00:13:15,640 --> 00:13:19,520
Falah? Yes.
The one who's always with Fateh.

163
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:22,359
Did you know that
he went missing last night?

164
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:24,319
Missing?

165
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:25,919
I didn't hear anything.

166
00:13:25,920 --> 00:13:29,079
But that's normal around here.

167
00:13:29,080 --> 00:13:32,039
Whenever they get bored of staying here,
they run away.

168
00:13:32,040 --> 00:13:35,720
So, you're saying he ran away?
Not missing?

169
00:13:37,960 --> 00:13:40,039
I don't know, Ridz.

170
00:13:40,040 --> 00:13:42,039
Ever since I started working here,

171
00:13:42,040 --> 00:13:45,840
I've never heard of children
going missing.

172
00:13:50,920 --> 00:13:52,760
That's what happened to my mother.

173
00:13:54,160 --> 00:13:59,280
She kept everything inside,
even when she's angry, sad, or sick.

174
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:02,840
It was disguised under her smile.

175
00:14:03,520 --> 00:14:05,960
She didn't want us to worry.

176
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:12,720
She knew she's the only one we had.

177
00:14:19,920 --> 00:14:21,920
One night,

178
00:14:22,640 --> 00:14:24,600
around 2 a.m.,

179
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:29,759
my brother had a high fever
and my dad wasn't home.

180
00:14:29,760 --> 00:14:31,800
He was in the middle of an operation.

181
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:37,440
Mom called him. She was having chest pain.

182
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:40,240
He didn't pick up.

183
00:14:42,480 --> 00:14:46,400
She was worried about my brother.
So, she took him to the hospital.

184
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:49,800
On her way,

185
00:14:52,920 --> 00:14:55,120
she passed out while driving.

186
00:14:56,640 --> 00:14:58,840
The car skidded and crashed into a tree.

187
00:15:00,880 --> 00:15:03,320
They both died on the spot.

188
00:15:07,080 --> 00:15:09,760
Did you know what was the worst part?

189
00:15:12,760 --> 00:15:16,320
My dad only came back after three days.

190
00:15:18,520 --> 00:15:20,480
Only for half a day.

191
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:23,880
Later that day, he went back to work.

192
00:15:26,720 --> 00:15:29,560
Did they not give him
any compassionate leave?

193
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:31,960
They couldn't be that mean.

194
00:15:33,520 --> 00:15:35,599
It turned out

195
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:38,240
that while he was away on operations,

196
00:15:38,840 --> 00:15:41,000
he wasn't actually serving his country.

197
00:15:42,040 --> 00:15:44,320
But it was for his lust.

198
00:15:46,320 --> 00:15:49,480
He had a second wife, secretly.

199
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:53,400
They were in the same unit.

200
00:15:56,200 --> 00:15:59,960
I've been keeping all this
to myself for a while.

201
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:05,520
It feels good to be able to talk about it.

202
00:16:08,120 --> 00:16:11,120
My husband and I are not the same.

203
00:16:13,240 --> 00:16:15,600
Do you think I can be happy with him?

204
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:20,160
Why are you asking me that?

205
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:22,600
Did something happen at home?

206
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:31,239
- I don't think he ran away.
- Then, he must be missing?

207
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:33,519
I'm not sure about that.

208
00:16:33,520 --> 00:16:37,679
I heard that missing children
at Teduh often went missing.

209
00:16:37,680 --> 00:16:39,519
Is that true?

210
00:16:39,520 --> 00:16:42,800
They come and go all the time.

211
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:44,800
I don't think anyone ever went missing.

212
00:16:47,160 --> 00:16:49,840
Saifuddin, wait!

213
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:55,520
Ridz, how are you?

214
00:16:57,320 --> 00:17:00,200
He wanted to know
if there's a kid missing from here.

215
00:17:01,040 --> 00:17:02,800
Did you hear anything about it?

216
00:17:03,480 --> 00:17:07,760
I'm not sure about that.
I'm not here all the time.

217
00:17:09,359 --> 00:17:11,440
I should get going. I have things to do.

218
00:17:27,200 --> 00:17:31,439
My mom asked me to divorce Ridz,

219
00:17:31,440 --> 00:17:36,160
so that he can marry Raudhah
because she's pregnant.

220
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:40,520
I don't know what else to think.
I can't even make a decision.

221
00:17:43,560 --> 00:17:45,920
But do you want to divorce him?

222
00:17:46,760 --> 00:17:49,719
And let him marry Raudhah?

223
00:17:49,720 --> 00:17:53,160
Even though he wasn't the one
who got her pregnant?

224
00:17:53,800 --> 00:17:57,160
It seems like that's the only thing
that will make everyone happy.

225
00:17:58,240 --> 00:18:00,840
Okay. But will you be happy?

226
00:18:04,880 --> 00:18:06,079
Psycho.

227
00:18:06,080 --> 00:18:08,000
No, sorry.

228
00:18:08,680 --> 00:18:10,199
Toxic.

229
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:11,720
Did you know that your family is toxic?

230
00:18:13,080 --> 00:18:16,440
- I do.
- How did they even think of that?

231
00:18:18,280 --> 00:18:20,840
Because they are after his money.

232
00:18:21,480 --> 00:18:23,880
So, it's true then. They're psychopaths.

233
00:18:26,600 --> 00:18:29,879
Should I just give in?

234
00:18:29,880 --> 00:18:34,200
I feel like my marriage
has been through so much.

235
00:18:34,800 --> 00:18:35,720
Give in?

236
00:18:37,280 --> 00:18:38,760
What do you gain from giving in?

237
00:18:39,320 --> 00:18:42,040
I don't know. Probably nothing.

238
00:18:42,920 --> 00:18:46,000
Then, don't.

239
00:18:47,320 --> 00:18:50,520
You should only give in
when you have something to gain.

240
00:19:06,520 --> 00:19:09,439
Before I send you to meet the Grim Reaper,

241
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:12,279
you'd better tell me
where the children are.

242
00:19:12,280 --> 00:19:13,199
I don't know.

243
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:16,839
All I know is that this place is just
a transit point for them.

244
00:19:16,840 --> 00:19:18,200
Transit?

245
00:19:19,520 --> 00:19:20,600
Where to?

246
00:19:21,640 --> 00:19:23,280
Answer my questions!

247
00:19:24,600 --> 00:19:26,879
I think they've been sold off to Thailand.

248
00:19:26,880 --> 00:19:28,240
To be beggars.

249
00:19:28,920 --> 00:19:30,320
Damn you...

250
00:19:39,920 --> 00:19:42,000
Why didn't you answer my call?

251
00:19:44,120 --> 00:19:45,600
What for?

252
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:50,120
To listen to you cursing at me?

253
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:55,079
You've been acting worse
since you got married.

254
00:19:55,080 --> 00:19:58,599
You're doing this
to your own family on purpose.

255
00:19:58,600 --> 00:20:00,280
You're a useless daughter!

256
00:20:02,560 --> 00:20:04,840
You're brave enough to fight me back now.

257
00:20:05,520 --> 00:20:09,639
Hey, listen to me!
I want you to agree to divorce Thariq

258
00:20:09,640 --> 00:20:12,000
and ask him to marry your sister!

259
00:20:12,840 --> 00:20:15,280
No way. Never.

260
00:20:16,720 --> 00:20:21,120
Why do I have to sacrifice
the only good thing in my life?

261
00:20:23,040 --> 00:20:25,600
Don't you want me to be happy at all?

262
00:20:26,680 --> 00:20:28,559
Happy?

263
00:20:28,560 --> 00:20:31,039
Now, you'd better choose

264
00:20:31,040 --> 00:20:35,960
between happiness and my forgiveness.

265
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:41,439
You will forgive me about...

266
00:20:41,440 --> 00:20:44,919
Yes, about that incident 15 years ago!

267
00:20:44,920 --> 00:20:48,159
I will forget everything!

268
00:20:48,160 --> 00:20:50,200
What happened 15 years ago?

269
00:20:52,440 --> 00:20:55,600
I don't want to hear
anything else right now.

270
00:20:56,240 --> 00:20:58,880
Now, I want you to agree.

271
00:20:59,960 --> 00:21:01,560
I'll be waiting for your answer.

272
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:11,000
Darling.

273
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:16,840
Darling, tell me.

274
00:21:17,400 --> 00:21:22,400
What happened 15 years ago that
you wanted her forgiveness so badly?

275
00:21:23,040 --> 00:21:25,200
Darling, please.

276
00:21:26,400 --> 00:21:30,480
Darling, how am I going
to help if you won't tell me?

277
00:21:31,280 --> 00:21:34,640
It's like I'm doing this on my own.

278
00:21:35,480 --> 00:21:38,240
I'm trying to protect you,
but I don't know from what.

279
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:41,039
This is my problem.

280
00:21:41,040 --> 00:21:43,519
Mine! This has nothing to do with you.

281
00:21:43,520 --> 00:21:46,920
So, please. Stay out of this.

282
00:21:48,880 --> 00:21:50,999
You're my wife.

283
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:54,759
Your problem is my problem.
Your pain is my pain too.

284
00:21:54,760 --> 00:21:58,280
No, you're wrong! You have nothing
to do with this. So, please.

285
00:22:04,080 --> 00:22:06,000
Why is it so hard to tell me?

286
00:22:06,760 --> 00:22:09,400
We're husband and wife.
There should be no secrets between us.

287
00:22:10,920 --> 00:22:13,879
Please, don't push me.

288
00:22:13,880 --> 00:22:16,320
Do you think acting like this
can solve my problem?

289
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:19,560
Yeah. You're right.

290
00:22:22,640 --> 00:22:23,720
I'm sorry.

291
00:22:26,880 --> 00:22:28,880
I won't ask anything anymore.

292
00:22:42,360 --> 00:22:45,359
<i>Yes, about that incident 15 years ago!</i>

293
00:22:45,360 --> 00:22:48,160
<i>I will forget everything.</i>

294
00:22:55,040 --> 00:22:57,520
Sorry to keep you waiting.

295
00:22:58,920 --> 00:23:02,680
You came too early.
The cafe is not even open yet.

296
00:23:03,920 --> 00:23:05,840
Here's your favorite coffee.

297
00:23:07,320 --> 00:23:13,080
The other day, you told me not to give in
unless I had something to gain.

298
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:15,560
Yes, that's true.

299
00:23:17,120 --> 00:23:19,400
What if by giving in,

300
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:23,120
I gain something that
I've been wanting for so long?

301
00:23:30,920 --> 00:23:31,800
What do you mean?

302
00:23:33,640 --> 00:23:38,480
My mom offered me something
that I've always wanted.

303
00:23:40,400 --> 00:23:43,360
For a long time, even before I met Ridz.

304
00:23:44,640 --> 00:23:49,640
But if I want it, I have to let Ridz go.

305
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:55,320
Is it worth it to let Ridz go
just to have that?

306
00:23:57,480 --> 00:23:58,960
I don't know.

307
00:24:01,800 --> 00:24:05,639
Have you ever heard
that if we love something,

308
00:24:05,640 --> 00:24:07,960
we have to let it go?

309
00:24:13,520 --> 00:24:15,480
Should I let him go?

310
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:18,600
You want my answer?

311
00:24:23,320 --> 00:24:24,480
I'll give it to you tomorrow.

312
00:24:25,560 --> 00:24:27,120
Why tomorrow?

313
00:24:27,760 --> 00:24:31,400
If I answer now,

314
00:24:32,160 --> 00:24:35,480
you might not want
to see me again tomorrow.

315
00:24:52,240 --> 00:24:55,440
Seriously, I didn't expect this to happen.

316
00:24:56,040 --> 00:25:00,520
I've heard news about children
being kidnapped and forced to beg.

317
00:25:02,360 --> 00:25:05,319
I didn't expect this.
I should have been more alert.

318
00:25:05,320 --> 00:25:09,319
- I failed to save them.
- Okay. It's not your fault.

319
00:25:09,320 --> 00:25:11,119
It was Zahid's fault.

320
00:25:11,120 --> 00:25:14,200
He's been using you and Teduh
for his dirty work.

321
00:25:17,240 --> 00:25:20,520
Then what are we going to do
if this keeps happening?

322
00:25:21,840 --> 00:25:23,400
Calm down.

323
00:25:24,320 --> 00:25:26,000
Don't worry.

324
00:25:27,840 --> 00:25:31,640
From now on,
my team and I will monitor Teduh.

325
00:25:33,440 --> 00:25:34,880
Please.

326
00:25:45,040 --> 00:25:46,440
Darling?

327
00:25:49,200 --> 00:25:50,720
Darling?

328
00:25:54,400 --> 00:25:56,520
Where is he?

329
00:26:13,840 --> 00:26:15,799
<i>This is my problem.</i>

330
00:26:15,800 --> 00:26:18,839
<i>Mine! This has nothing to do with you.</i>

331
00:26:18,840 --> 00:26:22,199
<i>So, please. Stay out of this.</i>

332
00:26:22,200 --> 00:26:24,359
<i>You're my wife.</i>

333
00:26:24,360 --> 00:26:27,880
<i>Your problem is my problem.
Your pain is my pain too.</i>

334
00:26:30,680 --> 00:26:32,480
I'm sorry, dear.

335
00:26:34,400 --> 00:26:36,440
I was too much.

336
00:26:57,040 --> 00:26:59,040
- Do you want coffee?
- I want your answer.

337
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:04,360
My answer is...

338
00:27:05,600 --> 00:27:08,080
if you really love someone,

339
00:27:09,320 --> 00:27:10,560
don't let them go.

340
00:27:11,960 --> 00:27:13,160
Fight.

341
00:27:14,040 --> 00:27:16,200
Don't ever give up.

342
00:27:18,360 --> 00:27:21,440
Fight until you don't love them anymore.

343
00:27:23,360 --> 00:27:26,120
When love turns to hate,

344
00:27:28,520 --> 00:27:31,040
maybe only then can you let him go.

345
00:27:33,240 --> 00:27:35,200
If you really love Ridz,

346
00:27:36,720 --> 00:27:38,280
settle with him.

347
00:27:39,600 --> 00:27:41,040
Tell him.

348
00:27:42,240 --> 00:27:43,600
Not me.

349
00:27:44,920 --> 00:27:46,400
Thank you.

350
00:27:49,440 --> 00:27:52,680
But you could have answered me yesterday.

351
00:27:53,240 --> 00:27:54,920
Why insist on doing it today?

352
00:27:55,760 --> 00:28:00,080
Because I know if I did it yesterday,

353
00:28:00,640 --> 00:28:02,960
I won't get to see you again.

354
00:28:05,440 --> 00:28:07,080
Why would you think that?

355
00:28:07,840 --> 00:28:13,600
You once told me that
you felt guilty for coming to see me.

356
00:28:15,800 --> 00:28:17,160
So I hope

357
00:28:17,960 --> 00:28:21,719
I will never have to save you

358
00:28:21,720 --> 00:28:23,880
from any unfortunate events anymore.

359
00:28:27,280 --> 00:28:28,720
Thank you.

360
00:28:45,240 --> 00:28:46,240
Bye, Radwa.

361
00:28:48,680 --> 00:28:52,120
Don't ever come again.

362
00:29:02,040 --> 00:29:05,279
Dad, what's so important
that we had to meet here?

363
00:29:05,280 --> 00:29:07,480
We could have just met at home.

364
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:12,000
Also, does Mom know
you're meeting me here?

365
00:29:13,920 --> 00:29:15,040
No.

366
00:29:16,280 --> 00:29:19,840
Actually, I missed you so much.

367
00:29:20,840 --> 00:29:22,720
That's why I wanted to see you.

368
00:29:24,440 --> 00:29:25,920
Radwa,

369
00:29:27,680 --> 00:29:29,000
I want to apologize.

370
00:29:30,240 --> 00:29:32,680
We shouldn't have done this to you.

371
00:29:35,720 --> 00:29:39,800
I don't even know how this happened.

372
00:29:41,280 --> 00:29:44,680
Raudhah won't even say who the father is.

373
00:29:45,800 --> 00:29:48,360
And the way your Mom behaves.

374
00:29:50,640 --> 00:29:52,919
I'm sorry.

375
00:29:52,920 --> 00:29:56,040
I'm sorry for not defending you.

376
00:29:59,400 --> 00:30:01,279
It's fine, Dad.

377
00:30:01,280 --> 00:30:02,880
Too many things happened all of a sudden.

378
00:30:04,040 --> 00:30:06,839
Sometimes, you have to choose
the easiest way.

379
00:30:06,840 --> 00:30:08,240
What do you mean?

380
00:30:09,880 --> 00:30:11,880
Didn't Ridz tell you?

381
00:30:13,680 --> 00:30:15,640
I saw him last month.

382
00:30:18,840 --> 00:30:20,320
I'm sorry

383
00:30:22,080 --> 00:30:24,880
for asking this from you.

384
00:30:26,680 --> 00:30:28,240
I don't have a choice.

385
00:30:30,160 --> 00:30:31,760
Mom was pushing me.

386
00:30:34,920 --> 00:30:36,720
Who was the father?

387
00:30:37,680 --> 00:30:39,000
I don't know.

388
00:30:40,560 --> 00:30:42,320
I asked her many times.

389
00:30:43,160 --> 00:30:44,680
She never said anything.

390
00:30:47,800 --> 00:30:49,040
Ridz,

391
00:30:50,040 --> 00:30:51,280
help us.

392
00:30:52,560 --> 00:30:57,120
You're the only one
who can help our family.

393
00:31:01,160 --> 00:31:04,280
I hope you won't tell Radwa about this.

394
00:31:05,320 --> 00:31:07,440
Let me tell her myself.

395
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:10,200
Is that okay?

396
00:31:11,760 --> 00:31:12,920
Okay.

397
00:31:17,520 --> 00:31:21,360
No, he did tell me. He did.

398
00:31:21,960 --> 00:31:23,640
I'm not trying to pressure you.

399
00:31:24,400 --> 00:31:27,400
But if possible,

400
00:31:28,360 --> 00:31:29,640
please consider.

401
00:31:41,440 --> 00:31:43,360
Aren't you eating with me?

402
00:31:51,440 --> 00:31:52,800
Are you feeling better?

403
00:31:57,800 --> 00:31:59,840
I'm asking you. Are you feeling better?

404
00:32:00,840 --> 00:32:04,200
Husbands and wives shouldn't
keep secrets, right?

405
00:32:06,120 --> 00:32:08,400
But you are keeping secrets from me.

406
00:32:11,280 --> 00:32:12,720
What do you mean?

407
00:32:13,640 --> 00:32:15,560
Have you been keeping
too many secrets from me?

408
00:32:16,480 --> 00:32:18,200
Darling, what's this?

409
00:32:18,960 --> 00:32:22,040
Why didn't you tell me that
you already knew about Mom's plan?

410
00:32:22,640 --> 00:32:24,999
A month ago, Dad already told you
that Raudhah was pregnant

411
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:27,080
and that they wanted you to marry her.

412
00:32:30,840 --> 00:32:32,360
Let's not do this in front of the food.

413
00:32:33,760 --> 00:32:35,760
It's not nice.

414
00:32:38,080 --> 00:32:40,000
I didn't tell you...

415
00:32:41,320 --> 00:32:44,320
because I don't want you
to be sad, angry, or stressed.

416
00:32:45,720 --> 00:32:47,239
Look at you now.

417
00:32:47,240 --> 00:32:49,079
You're mad at me.

418
00:32:49,080 --> 00:32:51,799
I only did that to protect you.

419
00:32:51,800 --> 00:32:54,000
I don't want to hurt you.

420
00:32:57,760 --> 00:33:00,640
What difference does it make?
I found out anyway.

421
00:33:05,560 --> 00:33:07,160
Didn't Dad tell you?

422
00:33:07,760 --> 00:33:09,799
How I rejected Mom's plan?

423
00:33:09,800 --> 00:33:11,319
That's why I didn't tell you.

424
00:33:11,320 --> 00:33:13,399
But why did you keep it a secret?

425
00:33:13,400 --> 00:33:16,159
Can you not play the victim now?

426
00:33:16,160 --> 00:33:19,159
You were the one keeping secrets from me.

427
00:33:19,160 --> 00:33:23,040
You didn't tell me
about what happened 15 years ago.

428
00:33:24,080 --> 00:33:28,000
Your secret is like cancer
that's slowly ruining our relationship.

429
00:33:32,680 --> 00:33:35,320
I won't push you.

430
00:33:36,080 --> 00:33:38,359
I offered you space, to help you.

431
00:33:38,360 --> 00:33:40,880
But if this space hurts you,

432
00:33:43,840 --> 00:33:45,440
I'm sorry.

433
00:34:12,480 --> 00:34:14,600
This is my problem.

434
00:34:15,159 --> 00:34:17,519
Mine! This has nothing to do with you.

435
00:34:17,520 --> 00:34:20,559
So, please. Stay out of this.

436
00:34:20,560 --> 00:34:24,440
You didn't tell me
about what happened 15 years ago.

437
00:34:25,560 --> 00:34:29,239
Your secret is like cancer
that's slowly ruining our relationship.

438
00:34:33,400 --> 00:34:35,600
If you really love Ridz,

439
00:34:36,960 --> 00:34:38,080
settle with him.

440
00:34:39,719 --> 00:34:41,239
Tell him.

441
00:34:42,440 --> 00:34:43,760
Not me.

442
00:35:13,360 --> 00:35:15,080
Peace be upon you.

443
00:35:32,200 --> 00:35:33,360
I'm sorry.

444
00:35:38,080 --> 00:35:39,960
I know I was wrong.

445
00:35:42,480 --> 00:35:44,080
I shouldn't have pushed you.

446
00:35:48,400 --> 00:35:49,680
No.

447
00:35:51,200 --> 00:35:52,560
You were right.

448
00:35:54,480 --> 00:35:57,440
This secret is ruining our relationship.

449
00:36:03,040 --> 00:36:04,600
I'm ready...

450
00:36:06,320 --> 00:36:09,880
to tell you what happened 15 years ago.

451
00:36:15,320 --> 00:36:16,800
Actually,

452
00:36:18,160 --> 00:36:20,240
I had a younger brother.

453
00:36:22,080 --> 00:36:23,720
His name was Raiza.

454
00:36:37,440 --> 00:36:38,840
It was the night before Eid.

455
00:36:39,960 --> 00:36:42,760
<i>Dad and Mom hadn't managed
to buy their clothes for Eid yet.</i>

456
00:36:44,440 --> 00:36:47,160
<i>All of us went out together.</i>

457
00:36:48,360 --> 00:36:52,280
<i>At the boutique, Ridha
and Raudhah wouldn't stop fighting.</i>

458
00:36:52,880 --> 00:36:56,039
<i>Dad tried to calm them down.</i>

459
00:36:56,040 --> 00:36:58,520
<i>Mom was busy picking clothes.</i>

460
00:36:59,200 --> 00:37:01,320
<i>My brother was asking for her attention.</i>

461
00:37:02,320 --> 00:37:04,519
<i>But she ignored him.</i>

462
00:37:04,520 --> 00:37:07,599
<i>While waiting, he ran away.</i>

463
00:37:07,600 --> 00:37:10,559
- Look at her.
- Dad, look at her!

464
00:37:10,560 --> 00:37:12,039
Raiza?

465
00:37:12,040 --> 00:37:14,039
Gosh!

466
00:37:14,040 --> 00:37:15,319
Raiza?

467
00:37:15,320 --> 00:37:17,200
<i>When I went after him,</i>

468
00:37:18,960 --> 00:37:20,240
<i>I saw him being kidnapped.</i>

469
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:23,120
Raiza!

470
00:37:26,720 --> 00:37:27,800
Help!

471
00:37:29,160 --> 00:37:31,719
Raiza!

472
00:37:31,720 --> 00:37:33,240
Radwa, where's Raiza?

473
00:37:36,760 --> 00:37:38,039
Raiza?

474
00:37:38,040 --> 00:37:41,079
- Why did you let him go?
- Where is he?

475
00:37:41,080 --> 00:37:44,040
He was kidnapped!

476
00:37:44,880 --> 00:37:47,079
Kidnapped?

477
00:37:47,080 --> 00:37:50,319
You couldn't even
look after him for a while?

478
00:37:50,320 --> 00:37:51,680
What's wrong with you?

479
00:38:00,920 --> 00:38:04,360
Now, do you understand
why I didn't want to tell you?

480
00:38:06,720 --> 00:38:08,079
I'm a murderer.

481
00:38:08,080 --> 00:38:10,080
I killed my own brother.

482
00:38:13,280 --> 00:38:15,480
You're not a murderer.

483
00:38:16,560 --> 00:38:19,120
I'm sure you regret marrying me.

484
00:38:19,760 --> 00:38:21,799
If you want to leave me, I'll accept it.

485
00:38:21,800 --> 00:38:23,920
Darling, listen.

486
00:38:24,800 --> 00:38:26,240
Not even a little bit.

487
00:38:28,960 --> 00:38:31,000
Don't you hate me?

488
00:38:34,000 --> 00:38:36,040
Why would I hate you?

489
00:38:38,120 --> 00:38:40,360
I already heard the truth from you.

490
00:38:40,920 --> 00:38:43,360
And now I know how to protect you.

491
00:38:46,120 --> 00:38:47,920
Darling, listen.

492
00:38:48,960 --> 00:38:50,400
I swear

493
00:38:51,320 --> 00:38:53,119
and promise,

494
00:38:53,120 --> 00:38:57,320
as long as you want to be my wife,
I won't leave you.

495
00:39:01,640 --> 00:39:03,320
I am...

496
00:39:04,480 --> 00:39:06,080
yours.

497
00:39:07,720 --> 00:39:09,280
Forever.

498
00:39:15,400 --> 00:39:17,120
Dear.

499
00:39:19,040 --> 00:39:20,680
One more thing.

500
00:39:25,960 --> 00:39:28,519
I want to apologize

501
00:39:28,520 --> 00:39:31,160
for leaving the house
without your permission.

502
00:39:36,680 --> 00:39:37,880
I forgive you.

503
00:39:40,240 --> 00:39:43,039
- It's not a big deal.
- No, dear.

504
00:39:43,040 --> 00:39:46,279
- I'm really sorry.
- Darling, listen.

505
00:39:46,280 --> 00:39:48,160
I forgive you.

506
00:39:49,400 --> 00:39:52,319
Unless you went out and didn't ask
for my money, then that's weird.

507
00:39:52,320 --> 00:39:53,760
That's dangerous.

508
00:39:54,640 --> 00:39:57,039
Okay? Now, it's late.

509
00:39:57,040 --> 00:39:59,360
Let's pray together.

510
00:40:01,000 --> 00:40:02,560
Come on.

511
00:40:05,240 --> 00:40:07,320
Don't cry anymore.

512
00:40:08,640 --> 00:40:10,760
Forget about it. It's okay.

513
00:40:11,600 --> 00:40:12,960
I understand.

514
00:40:14,200 --> 00:40:15,440
Hurry up.

515
00:40:16,240 --> 00:40:18,200
They're complaining about the shortage.

516
00:40:21,080 --> 00:40:23,200
They've been stuck
at the border for a few days.

517
00:40:24,720 --> 00:40:27,479
Make sure this thing settles tonight.

518
00:40:27,480 --> 00:40:29,799
Follow the route I just told you.

519
00:40:29,800 --> 00:40:31,360
Let's go!

520
00:40:39,800 --> 00:40:41,599
So? Is everything enough?

521
00:40:41,600 --> 00:40:42,720
Yes, Datin.

522
00:40:43,440 --> 00:40:45,319
I'll make sure to settle it tonight.

523
00:40:45,320 --> 00:40:46,760
Good.

524
00:40:47,600 --> 00:40:48,599
One more thing.

525
00:40:48,600 --> 00:40:51,759
You know Thariq
is investigating all this, right?

526
00:40:51,760 --> 00:40:54,520
Be careful. Don't get caught.

527
00:40:55,360 --> 00:40:56,360
All right, Datin.

528
00:41:08,040 --> 00:41:09,800
Praise be to God.

529
00:41:13,200 --> 00:41:15,240
- Dear.
- Yes?

530
00:41:15,960 --> 00:41:17,680
I want to apologize

531
00:41:18,280 --> 00:41:21,240
from the top of your head
to the tips of your toes.

532
00:41:22,160 --> 00:41:24,120
You did nothing wrong, darling.

533
00:41:25,840 --> 00:41:27,000
But wait.

534
00:41:27,840 --> 00:41:29,919
Why my feet?
What do they have to do with it?

535
00:41:29,920 --> 00:41:31,639
Because my legs are short.

536
00:41:31,640 --> 00:41:32,960
So my legs are long then?

537
00:41:33,960 --> 00:41:35,240
I see.

538
00:41:37,400 --> 00:41:40,680
Dear, do you want to see Raiza's picture?

539
00:41:41,280 --> 00:41:42,960
Of course.

540
00:41:59,440 --> 00:42:00,760
Fateh?

541
00:42:01,960 --> 00:42:03,479
Similar, isn't it?

542
00:42:03,480 --> 00:42:05,879
Now I understand why

543
00:42:05,880 --> 00:42:09,799
you're always at Teduh,

544
00:42:09,800 --> 00:42:13,000
and treat Fateh like your own brother.

545
00:42:15,240 --> 00:42:19,440
I feel like Raiza is close by
when I'm with Fateh.

546
00:42:25,440 --> 00:42:26,880
{\an8}Answer it.

547
00:42:31,520 --> 00:42:33,200
Go on.

548
00:42:38,800 --> 00:42:39,960
Hello.

549
00:42:42,320 --> 00:42:43,520
Okay, I'll be on my way.

550
00:42:47,000 --> 00:42:50,200
- Operation?
- Yes, operation.

551
00:42:51,160 --> 00:42:53,359
I have to get ready.

552
00:42:53,360 --> 00:42:55,640
Okay? Let's go.

553
00:43:00,640 --> 00:43:02,080
Come on.

554
00:43:05,920 --> 00:43:07,680
Peace be upon you.

555
00:43:36,600 --> 00:43:38,320
Radwa?

556
00:43:51,960 --> 00:43:53,840
Darling?

557
00:44:00,000 --> 00:44:01,519
Come with me.

558
00:44:01,520 --> 00:44:02,880
Goodness.

559
00:44:07,080 --> 00:44:09,719
Slowly, darling.

560
00:44:09,720 --> 00:44:11,320
Don't touch me!

561
00:44:13,040 --> 00:44:15,879
Darling, I swear
I didn't do all that, okay?

562
00:44:15,880 --> 00:44:18,559
Why was I so stupid to trust you?

563
00:44:18,560 --> 00:44:22,239
I gave you my whole life!
I was loyal to you!

564
00:44:22,240 --> 00:44:24,999
And you did this behind my back?

565
00:44:25,000 --> 00:44:28,239
Be angry all you want.
Let's go to the clinic.

566
00:44:28,240 --> 00:44:30,719
Divorce me.

567
00:44:30,720 --> 00:44:32,200
Thariq Ridzuwan.

568
00:44:35,600 --> 00:44:37,680
Darling?

569
00:44:39,160 --> 00:44:40,080
Darling?

570
00:44:42,440 --> 00:44:43,400
Darling...

571
00:44:50,000 --> 00:44:51,240
- Sorry, sir. Please wait outside.
- Nurse...

572
00:45:11,960 --> 00:45:16,360
{\an8}TO BE CONTINUED

573
00:45:22,760 --> 00:45:26,079
{\an8}I don't have time! I only have an hour.

574
00:45:26,080 --> 00:45:28,040
{\an8}Please don't waste my time.

575
00:45:28,800 --> 00:45:31,159
{\an8}Follow me if you want.
Otherwise, stay here.

576
00:45:31,160 --> 00:45:33,320
{\an8}<i>You're running out of time, Ridz.</i>

577
00:45:33,840 --> 00:45:37,440
{\an8}If anything happens to Fateh,
Radwa will never forgive me.

578
00:45:38,440 --> 00:45:39,920
{\an8}Dear?

579
00:45:42,760 --> 00:45:45,160
{\an8}Oh, God!

580
00:45:45,840 --> 00:45:49,439
{\an8}Haider!

581
00:45:49,440 --> 00:45:51,119
{\an8}And I believe

582
00:45:51,120 --> 00:45:54,400
{\an8}fate has determined
I'm the man who'll protect you.

583
00:45:55,280 --> 00:45:57,599
{\an8}See what your stubbornness did?

584
00:45:57,600 --> 00:45:59,439
{\an8}Forgive me, Thalia.

585
00:45:59,440 --> 00:46:01,319
{\an8}No.

586
00:46:01,320 --> 00:46:03,440
{\an8}You're selfish!

